<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <base href="/" />

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    @* Webfonts the built-in styles ask for by family name (the engine only emits the
       family stack + textLength guards — the host page must actually load them). Without
       these, the style gallery loses the typographic half of each identity: sketch falls
       back off Shantell Sans, brutalist/metro off Archivo, editorial off Source Serif 4. *@
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Archivo:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Shantell+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />

    @* Set the theme before first paint to avoid a flash of the wrong palette.
       MonorailCSS keys dark mode off the `.dark` class; every Beck SVG keys its
       theming off the ancestor `data-theme`. Set both up front. *@
    <script>
        (function () {
            try {
                var stored = localStorage.getItem('theme');
                var dark = stored ? stored === 'dark' : matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
                var root = document.documentElement;
                root.classList.toggle('dark', dark);
                root.setAttribute('data-theme', dark ? 'dark' : 'light');
            } catch (e) { document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', 'light'); }
        })();
    </script>

    @* MonorailCSS runtime stylesheet (utilities + ExtraStyles). *@
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />

    @* Monaco's stylesheet, declared statically. editor.main.js injects this link itself on a
       full page load, but Blazor enhanced navigation strips dynamically-injected head elements
       when merging the next page's head — arriving at /playground via a link click then boots
       Monaco with no CSS (broken layout, uneditable). Shipping the link in the SSR HTML keeps
       it alive across enhanced navigations. *@
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="_content/BlazorMonaco/lib/monaco-editor/min/vs/editor/editor.main.css" />

    @* Every diagram on the site is rendered to static SVG by the pure-C# engine — content
       ```beck fences at build time, the playground in the browser (WebAssembly). No client
       Beck JS engine is loaded. site.js only drives the theme toggle, copy buttons, and the
       small bits of page chrome (nav, syntax filter). *@
    <script src="/js/site.js" defer></script>
    @* Text metrics for the WASM playground's C# renderer (canvas measureText). Measurement
       only — the diagram itself is rendered by the C# engine compiled to WebAssembly. *@
    <script src="/js/beck-measure.js" defer></script>

    <HeadOutlet />
</head>
@* data-enhance-nav="false": every in-site link is a full page load. Blazor's enhanced
   navigation (blazor.web.js) DOM-merges the next page into the current one, which breaks
   the playground's Monaco editor three separate ways — it strips Monaco's dynamically
   injected stylesheet from <head>, swallows the editor's first paint (island activates
   against a mid-merge DOM), and strands the lazily-loaded YAML tokenizer in a module
   instance the live editor never consults (no syntax highlighting, no recovery). A full
   load is byte-identical to direct navigation, which works. The pages are static and
   small, and the theme is stamped before first paint, so nothing visibly regresses. *@
<body class="bg-white text-base-800 antialiased dark:bg-base-950 dark:text-base-100" data-enhance-nav="false">
    <Router AppAssembly="@typeof(App).Assembly">
        <Found Context="routeData">
            <RouteView RouteData="@routeData" DefaultLayout="@typeof(MainLayout)" />
        </Found>
        <NotFound>
            <MainLayout>
                <section class="mx-auto max-w-[1240px] px-8 py-20 text-center">
                    <div class="mb-5 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">404</div>
                    <h1 class="mb-3 text-4xl font-semibold text-base-900 dark:text-base-50">Page not found</h1>
                    <p class="text-base-600 dark:text-base-400">
                        The page you're looking for doesn't exist.
                        <a class="font-mono text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400" href="/">Back home →</a>
                    </p>
                </section>
            </MainLayout>
        </NotFound>
    </Router>

    @* Monaco (the playground editor): its interop shim + loader + editor bundle, served as
       static web assets by the BlazorMonaco package referenced through Beck.Docs.Client.
       Must precede the Blazor script so the editor JS is present when the WASM island boots. *@
    <script src="_content/BlazorMonaco/jsInterop.js"></script>
    <script src="_content/BlazorMonaco/lib/monaco-editor/min/vs/loader.js"></script>
    <script src="_content/BlazorMonaco/lib/monaco-editor/min/vs/editor/editor.main.js"></script>
    @* Reports the site theme to the playground editor so it can flip beck/beck-dark. *@
    <script src="/js/beck-editor.js" defer></script>

    @* Blazor runtime: boots the interactive-server circuit that backs the /playground
       component (server-side C# diagram rendering). Harmless on the static pages — they
       carry no interactive components — and on the static export it simply never connects. *@
    <script src="_framework/blazor.web.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
